    <title>
      With all the loud yelling, we wanted a space for loud listening
    </title>

    <description>
      We met Lizzie Kripke outside of both conventions, in the
      Philadelphia Public Library and a Cleveland shopping arcade,
      facilitating participation in the
      exhibit she helped create with Meg Saligman Studios, 
      "Our Common Ground: Vote for the Good
      Life."  The exhibit provided a
      space for respectful dialogue reframing the
      issues from an artistic point of view.
    </description>

